headline: 'We haven't seen the worst of it': Retailers warn tariff impacts are far from over
summary: Tariffs are driving up costs and straining consumers, leaving retailers from Walmart to Best Buy navigating an unpredictable spending environment.

headline: Hormel Foods Corporation (HRL) Just Has “Zero Pricing Power,” Says Jim Cramer

headline: Why Hormel Foods (HRL) Is Down 13.0% After Cutting 2025 Earnings Outlook Amid Profitability Concerns
summary: Earlier this week, Hormel Foods Corporation reported higher third-quarter sales and net income, but lowered its full-year 2025 earnings and operating income guidance, with GAAP diluted EPS now expected between US$1.33 and US$1.35 versus the prior US$1.49 to US$1.59. This shift highlights that, despite top-line growth, the company foresees increased challenges affecting profitability for the remainder of the year.
